Enum DocumentEZ.QStop

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<DocumentEZ.QStop>

    DocumentEZ

    public static enum DocumentEZ.QStop
extends java.lang.Enum<DocumentEZ.QStop>
    QStop options for use when feeding the paper

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      Back
      The printer will stop printing the set number of dotlines after the queue marks is found on the back of the media.
      Default
      The printer will act according to the value programmed into its internal flash memory.
      Front
      The printer will stop printing the set number of dotlines after the queue mark is found on the top of the media.
      Gap
      The printer will stop printing the set number of dotlines after the inter-label gap is found between labels.
      None
      The printer will ignore all queue stop settings in its internal flash memory and just print normally.

      • Default

        public static final DocumentEZ.QStop Default
        The printer will act according to the value programmed into its internal flash memory.

      • Front

        public static final DocumentEZ.QStop Front
        The printer will stop printing the set number of dotlines after the queue mark is found on the top of the media. This mode applies to the LP3, MF2T, MF3, 2t and 4t.

      • Back

        public static final DocumentEZ.QStop Back
        The printer will stop printing the set number of dotlines after the queue marks is found on the back of the media. This mode applies to the LP3.

      • Gap

        public static final DocumentEZ.QStop Gap
        The printer will stop printing the set number of dotlines after the inter-label gap is found between labels. This mode applies to the LP3.

      • None

        public static final DocumentEZ.QStop None
        The printer will ignore all queue stop settings in its internal flash memory and just print normally.
